This tarfile contains the following files:

        README          
        configfile    :  for the application 
        Makefile       
        CB.TOPO       : Topographic file of the Bay (Vis5D form)
        CBay.v5d.Z    : Vis5D file from numerical model output 
        CBay.v5d.SAVE : Sets up colors.
        ccpo.aud      : VSS audio config file [not used now] 
        src directory for cave5d

1.  You need to uncompress CBay.v5d.Z.
2.  Edit src/vis5d.h to reflect the memory you have available
	on the graphics machine (512Mb would be optimum for this
	application; if you have less, you may run out of memory).
3.  Make the app with the 'make debug' command.
4.  Run the app with the 'cave5d configfile' command.
5.  Standard CAVE wand navigation applies.  
6.  When the app comes up, the control panel should be used
	to start action.  Select a Mode (try 2)  and then animate.



